{"max_tokens":8192,"messages":[{"content":"You are a senior SystemVerilog verification engineer. Given the structured test plan, generate a complete SystemVerilog testbench. Include a clock generator, reset logic, basic scoreboard, and assertions. Output ONLY the raw SystemVerilog code without markdown formatting (no ```sv ... ```).","role":"system"},{"content":"{\n  \"module_name\": \"systolic_array\",\n  \"inputs\": [\n    {\n      \"name\": \"clk\",\n      \"width\": \"1-bit\",\n      \"description\": \"Positive edge clock signal\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"name\": \"rst_n\",\n      \"width\": \"1-bit\",\n      \"description\": \"Negative edge reset\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"name\": \"valid_in\",\n      \"width\": \"1-bit\",\n      \"description\": \"Valid signal set to 1 when valid data are settled on 'matrix_a_in' and 'matrix_b_in' so the DUT is allowed to sample them\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"name\": \"matrix_a_in\",\n      \"width\": \"N_SIZE * DATAWIDTH\",\n      \"description\": \"Array of N inputs corresponding to one column of matrix A elements entering the systolic array rows.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"name\": \"matrix_b_in\",\n      \"width\": \"N_SIZE * DATAWIDTH\",\n      \"description\": \"Array of N inputs corresponding to one row of matrix B elements entering the systolic array columns.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"outputs\": [\n    {\n      \"name\": \"valid_out\",\n      \"width\": \"1-bit\",\n      \"description\": \"Valid signal set to 1 when a valid row of the result matrix are settled on 'matrix_c_out'\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"name\": \"matrix_c_out\",\n      \"width\": \"N_SIZE * 2 * DATAWIDTH\",\n      \"description\": \"Array of 5 outputs corresponding to one row of matrix C elements resulting from the array multiplication\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"parameters\": [\n    {\n      \"name\": \"DATAWIDTH\",\n      \"type\": \"Integer\",\n      \"default_value\": \"16\",\n      \"description\": \"Datawidth of elements in in\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"name\": \"N_SIZE\",\n      \"type\": \"Integer\",\n      \"default_value\": \"5\",\n      \"description\": \"The size of the resulting matrix or the Number of PEs in each row or columns we assumed square matrix for simplicity\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"tests\": [\n    {\n      \"name\": \"reset_synchronous_active_low\",\n      \"type\": \"functional\",\n      \"description\": \"Verify that the design correctly resets all internal states and outputs when rst_n is asserted low, synchronized to the clock edge. All PEs should be cleared.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"name\": \"single_matrix_multiplication_3x3_valid_in_flow\",\n      \"type\": \"functional\",\n      \"description\": \"Apply a simple 3x3 matrix multiplication (e.g., A*B) using the specified input dataflow (matrix_a_in row-wise from left, matrix_b_in column-wise from top) and observe matrix_c_out. Monitor 'valid_in' and 'valid_out' signals to ensure correct data sampling and output timing according to Input/Output Dataflow diagram from page 5.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"name\": \"matrix_multiplication_N_SIZE_valid_in_flow\",\n      \"type\": \"functional\",\n      \"description\": \"Verify the matrix multiplication for an (N_SIZE x N_SIZE) scenario. Feed in a full set of 'matrix_a_in' and 'matrix_b_in' values according to the input dataflow and ensure 'matrix_c_out' contains the correct product with 'valid_out' assertion.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"name\": \"data_width_boundary_values\",\n      \"type\": \"functional\",\n      \"description\": \"Test the matrix multiplication with maximum and minimum representable values for DATAWIDTH (e.g., all 0s, all 1s, 2's complement boundaries) to ensure no overflow or underflow issues and correct propagation through PEs.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"name\": \"pipelined_data_flow_continuous_operation\",\n      \"type\": \"functional\",\n      \"description\": \"Verify the continuous data flow and parallel computation by continuously feeding new input matrices without any idle cycles. Ensure that output matrices appear at the correct intervals, demonstrating the pipeline's efficiency.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"name\": \"N_SIZE_parameter_config_5x5\",\n      \"type\": \"configuration_test\",\n      \"description\": \"Configure the N_SIZE parameter to 5 (default value) and verify that the systolic array functions correctly for 5x5 matrix multiplication. This implicitly checks the correct array dimensions and PE connectivity.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"name\": \"DATAWIDTH_parameter_config_16bit\",\n      \"type\": \"configuration_test\",\n      \"description\": \"Configure the DATAWIDTH parameter to 16 (default value) and verify that arithmetic operations within PEs handle 16-bit data correctly without truncation or sign extension issues for the given N_SIZE.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"name\": \"invalid_in_behavior\",\n      \"type\": \"error_handling\",\n      \"description\": \"Toggle 'valid_in' to 0 during matrix input to verify that the DUT ignores invalid data and maintains its current state or correctly handles the paused input stream. 'valid_out' should remain low.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"name\": \"random_matrix_multiplication\",\n      \"type\": \"random\",\n      \"description\": \"Generate random input matrices of appropriate dimensions and perform matrix multiplication. Compare the design's output with a golden reference model to ensure correctness over a wide range of inputs.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"name\": \"waveform_snapshot_comparison\",\n      \"type\": \"functional\",\n      \"description\": \"Run a specific test case (e.g., single 3x3 multiplication) and capture the waveform to compare against expected signal transitions for 'clk', 'rst_n', 'valid_in', 'valid_out', 'matrix_a_in', 'matrix_b_in', and 'matrix_c_out' as depicted in the specification's diagrams.\"\n    }\n  ]\n}","role":"user"}],"model":"meta-llama/llama-3.3-70b-instruct","response_format":{"type":"json_object"}}
