{"max_tokens":8192,"messages":[{"content":"You are a senior SystemVerilog verification engineer. Given the structured test plan, generate a complete SystemVerilog testbench. Include a clock generator, reset logic, basic scoreboard, and assertions. Output ONLY the raw SystemVerilog code without markdown formatting (no ```sv ... ```).","role":"system"},{"content":"{\n  \"module_name\": \"systolic_array\",\n  \"inputs\": [\n    {\n      \"name\": \"clk\",\n      \"width\": \"1-bit\",\n      \"description\": \"Positive edge clock signal\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"name\": \"rst_n\",\n      \"width\": \"1-bit\",\n      \"description\": \"Negative edge reset\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"name\": \"valid_in\",\n      \"width\": \"1-bit\",\n      \"description\": \"Valid signal set to 1 when a valid data are settled on 'matrix_a_in' and 'matrix_b_in' so the DUT is allowed to sample them\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"name\": \"matrix_a_in\",\n      \"width\": \"N_SIZE * DATAWIDTH\",\n      \"description\": \"Array of N inputs corresponding to one column of matrix A elements entering the systolic array rows.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"name\": \"matrix_b_in\",\n      \"width\": \"N_SIZE * DATAWIDTH\",\n      \"description\": \"Array of N inputs corresponding to one row of matrix B elements entering the systolic array columns.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"outputs\": [\n    {\n      \"name\": \"valid_out\",\n      \"width\": \"1-bit\",\n      \"description\": \"Valid signal set to 1 when a valid row of the result matrix are settled on 'matrix_c_out'\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"name\": \"matrix_c_out\",\n      \"width\": \"N_SIZE * 2 * DATAWIDTH\",\n      \"description\": \"Array of 5 outputs corresponding to one row of matrix C elements resulting from the array multiplication\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"tests\": [\n    {\n      \"name\": \"basic_matrix_multiplication\",\n      \"type\": \"functional\",\n      \"description\": \"Verify the basic functionality of the systolic array by performing a simple matrix multiplication. Input distinct values for matrix A and matrix B, assert valid_in, and check matrix_c_out against expected results. This test should cover the N_SIZE=5, DATAWIDTH=16 default parameters specified in the documentation. Simulate with one direct test case displaying input and output matrices as specified in the 'Simulation' requirements.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"name\": \"reset_synchronous\",\n      \"type\": \"control\",\n      \"description\": \"Test the synchronous reset functionality (rst_n). Apply reset during active data processing and observe if all internal states and outputs are correctly reset. Then, release reset and verify that the module resumes correct operation.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"name\": \"valid_in_control\",\n      \"type\": \"control\",\n      \"description\": \"Verify the behavior of 'valid_in' signal. Apply 'valid_in=1' for a specified number of clock cycles to allow sampling, then assert 'valid_in=0' and verify that the DUT does not sample new data. Ensure that 'valid_out' is asserted only when a valid output row is produced.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"name\": \"data_flow_timing\",\n      \"type\": \"timing\",\n      \"description\": \"Inspect the input and output dataflow timing based on the provided diagram 'Input/Output Dataflow'. Specifically, verify the data introduction over multiple clock cycles (e.g., '1st Clk Edge', '2nd Clk Edge', '3rd Clk Edge') and the corresponding 'valid_in' and 'valid_out' signals. Confirm that 'valid_in' is set to 0 when no new input data is available and 'valid_out' goes high when the first row of the output matrix is ready as shown on page 5.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"name\": \"param_N_SIZE\",\n      \"type\": \"functional\",\n      \"description\": \"Test the scalability of the systolic array by varying the N_SIZE parameter (e.g., N_SIZE = 3, N_SIZE = 4). Verify that the module correctly adapts to different matrix dimensions and performs multiplication for the new size. This requires overriding the default N_SIZE=5.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"name\": \"param_DATAWIDTH\",\n      \"type\": \"functional\",\n      \"description\": \"Test the module's behavior with different DATAWIDTH values (e.g., DATAWIDTH = 8, DATAWIDTH = 32). Ensure that the input and output ports are correctly sized and that the multiply-accumulate operations handle the new data width without overflow or truncation errors. This requires overriding the default DATAWIDTH=16.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"name\": \"pipelined_operation\",\n      \"type\": \"functional\",\n      \"description\": \"Verify the continuous data flow and parallel computation aspect of the pipeline. Feed contiguous streams of input matrices (A and B) and observe if the output matrix C is produced continuously after the initial latency, as implied by the 'pipeline enables continuous data flow' statement.\"\n    }\n  ]\n}","role":"user"}],"model":"meta-llama/llama-3.3-70b-instruct","response_format":{"type":"json_object"}}
